announcementBarSettings.text: Join us April 14 at 7:15 pm for our Good Friday Service.

upcoming.title: Women's Picnic + Afternoon of Prayer at Chanticleer Gardens
upcoming.body:
On May 7 (next Sunday), all women are invited to carpool to Chanticleer Gardens after the service. Admission to the gardens is $10, the grounds are stunning, and after we picnic together, we can break up into small groups and pray together. Or you can find a quiet place and pray alone.

This can also be an amazing outreach event. Do you have a hurting friend or neighbor? Would she like to come along, to be prayed for? The gardens are open until 5pm, so you can leave whenever is convenient for you.

For more information contact Kelly Estes.

upcoming.title: Young Lives Baby Bottle Fundraiser
upcoming.body: Iron Works is collecting funds in baby bottles to help support the work of YoungLives ministry. Through monthly meetings, Bible studies, mentoring relationships and summer camp, YoungLives seeks to give young mothers practical and emotional support, as well as share the Gospel. Collection begins Mothers Day (May 14) and concludes on Fathers Day (June 18).

past.title: Robbie Schmidtberger Installation Celebration
past.body:
Celebrate what God is doing in West Chester as Pastor Robbie Schmidtberger is installed as the lead pastor of Iron Works West Chester on April 30 at 5pm at IWWC, 312 W. Union St., West Chester. Nursery and refreshments will be provided.

past.title: Building Fundraiser: Parents' Night Out
past.body: Drop your kids off for a fun movie night in IronSpace each month while you enjoy time alone. Cost: $25 for first child; $15 for subsequent children; capped at $40/family. All proceeds go to the building fund. The first one, on March 29, is timed to coincide with the Iron Hill fundraiser.

past.body: On Wednesday, March 29, Iron Hill Brewery in Phoenixville will be setting aside 20 percent of all sales to those with Iron Works coupons to go the Iron Works building fund. Invite your friends and neighbors to enjoy delicious food while raising money to purchase our space!

past.body: Join with us as we express our appreciation for John and Ursula Orlando, who have faithfully served us as associate pastor and children's ministry director, respectively, during the past several years. We will celebrate with a lunch and a time of appreciation.

past.title: Community Cookie Decorating Party
past.body: Participate in an fun outreach event! IWC will host a community cookie decorating party in the Franklin Commons. We need volunteers to help with the preparations as well as hanging door flyers in the area. For more info or to sign up to help info@ironworkschurch.org.

past.title: Franklin Commons Christmas Party
past.body: We are hosting a Christmas party to serve our neighbors in Franklin Commons on Thursday, December 15 from 4pm-5:15pm! You can help out by dropping off a dessert (signup here) or by coming to the party to mingle and help serve food and drinks. For more information, contact info@ironworkschurch.org.

past.title: Pumpkinfest—Postponed to October 29
past.body: Phoenixville Pumpkinfest is a FREE fall festival held in downtown Phoenixville on Saturday, October 29 from 10:30am to 4:00pm. Phoenixville Pumpkinfest is hosted by RISE, a group of local Phoenixville churches, and is supported by local residents, businesses, and organizations. Iron Works does a great deal to put this festival on and so many volunteers are needed. If you'd like to help out the day of the event or with preparations beforehand, sign up here.

Iron Works does a great deal to put this festival on and so many volunteers are needed. If you'd like to help out the day of the event or with preparations beforehand, sign up here.

past.body: Join with other members of RISE churches as we pray that God would move mightily in Phoenixville through Pumpkinfest. We will meet in IronSpace for at time of prayer as we prepare to serve the town through this festival.

past.title: Supper for 8
past.body: Supper for 8 is a quarterly get-together for groups of about 8 to have a meal together. Hosts coordinate with groups to set a date and time within the quarter. Signup deadline is September 30. Fill out this form if you would like to participate.
past.excerpt: Supper for 8 is a quarterly get-together for groups of about 8 to have a meal together. Hosts coordinate with groups to set a date and time within the quarter. Signup deadline is July 6. Fill out this form if you would like to participate.

past.title: Pumpkinfest Workday II
past.body: Pumpkinfest—a fall town festival put on by RISE, a local coalition of churches—preparations continue. Everyone is invited to the final workday October 1 to accomplish a variety of preparatory tasks, from painting to supply-shopping. You can also sign up here to let the organizers know how you can help out on the day of the festival and what you're interested in helping with beforehand. This festival is for the whole town, so many volunteers are needed!

past.title: Pumpkinfest Workday I
past.body: Though it's not quite fall yet, planning for Pumpkinfest—a fall town festival put on by RISE, a local coalition of churches—has already begun. Everyone is invited to the first of two workdays August 20 to accomplish a variety of preparatory tasks, from painting to supply-shopping. If you can't make it on Aug. 20, you can also sign up here to let the organizers know what you're interested in and how you can help out on the day of the festival. This festival is for the whole town, so many volunteers are needed!
